question.questiontext:
Exercise

Write out the terms of the Fourier series for the periodic signal given by \[ f(t) = \begin{cases} 1 \hspace{1cm} 0 < t < \dfrac{\pi}{2} \\ 0 \hspace{1cm} \dfrac{\pi}{2} < t < 2\pi \end{cases} \] \[ f(t + 2\pi) = f(t)\] by filling in the boxes below. You should give the constant term \(\dfrac{a_0}{2}\) and each term corresponding to \( n = 1\) to \( n = 6\). The boxes below take the form \[ \begin{align} f(t) = \dfrac{a_0}{2} &+ a_1 \cos c_1 t + a_2 \cos c_2 t + a_3 \cos c_3 t + a_4 \cos c_4 t + a_5 \cos c_5 t + a_6 \cos c_6 t \\ &+ b_1 \sin c_1 t + b_2 \sin c_2 t + b_3 \sin c_3 t + b_4 \sin c_4 t + b_5 \sin c_5 t + b_6 \sin c_6 t \end{align} \]
